---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back</a>

    <!-- ── Hero ── -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <h1>AutoCurtain</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
          A curtain motor that raises and lowers your blinds automatically every morning and evening.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Feature Photo ── -->
    <div class="feature-image">
      <img src="/autocurtain-product.jpeg" alt="AutoCurtain mounted on curtain rod" />
    </div>

    <!-- ── Main Content ── -->
    <main>
      <h2 class="section-label">Overview</h2>
      <h3 class="section-title">AutoCurtain</h3>

      <p>
        Waking up at the same time every day is one of, if not the, most
        influential factors on your energy throughout the day. While automatic
        curtain raisers work greatly at waking you up more naturally than an
        alarm, products on the market often start at $300 and are not compatible
        with every curtain system.
      </p>

      <p>
        That is why I built a $50, universal curtain raiser that can be coupled
        to nearly any curtain on the market. The full BOM is under $50: a $1
        aluminum pipe, $5 lids, and a $20 12V DC gearmotor. Universality comes
        from the set screw shaft coupler, which clamps onto the curtain rod axle
        by tightening a set screw from the outside. It accepts any rod shaft
        under half an inch in diameter, which covers nearly every curtain system
        on the market.
      </p>

      <!-- ── CAD image pair ── -->
      <div class="image-pair">
        <figure>
          <img src="/autocurtain-gearbox.png" alt="Gearbox and motor assembly" />
          <figcaption>5:1 planetary gearbox &amp; 12V DC motor assembly</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img src="/autocurtain-body.png" alt="Main body cylinder" />
          <figcaption>Main body, Ø3.00″ × 4.93″ aluminum cylinder</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <h2 class="section-label" style="margin-top: 2.8rem;">Design</h2>

      <p>
        The main body is standard 3-inch aluminum tube stock, lightly sanded
        to a brushed finish. Using off-the-shelf pipe eliminated a turning
        operation and kept the cost down without sacrificing the look.
      </p>

      <p>
        Fitting a gearmotor coaxially inside a 3-inch bore rules out spur-gear
        sidepacks. A planetary stage solves this: the ring, planet, and sun
        gears all share the motor axis, so the entire drivetrain fits within
        the tube diameter. The 5:1 reduction multiplies torque enough to drive
        a loaded curtain from a standstill without stalling the motor.
      </p>

      <p>
        All structural parts were machined from aluminum on a Haas CNC VF2.
        Tight bore fits on the gearbox housing and the 8mm shaft coupler keep
        runout negligible over a long run life.
      </p>

      <!-- ── Cross-section ── -->
      <figure class="full-figure">
        <img src="/autocurtain-section.png" alt="Internal cross-section showing motor, gearbox, shaft coupler, and end plates" />
        <figcaption>Cross-section: 12V DC motor, 5:1 planetary gearbox, 8mm shaft coupler, aluminum end plates</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <!-- ── Specs Table ── -->
      <div class="specs-block">
        <div class="specs-label">Key Specifications</div>
        <table class="specs-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Motor</td>
              <td class="spec-val">12V DC brushed</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Gearbox</td>
              <td class="spec-val">5:1 planetary, coaxial, fits within Ø3.00″ bore</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Main Body</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Ø3.00″ OD × 4.93″ aluminum tube, brushed finish</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Material</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Aluminium, as machined</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Shaft Coupler</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Set screw type, accepts any rod up to ½″ diameter</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">BOM Cost</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Under $50 (vs. $200+ commercial)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Controller</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Arduino (timed relay)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Schedule</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Raise at 6:00 AM &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Lower at 11:00 PM</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="spec-key">Machined on</td>
              <td class="spec-val">Haas CNC VF2</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="status">Running daily since March 2026.</p>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }

  .page {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  .back-link {
    position: fixed;
    top: 2rem;
    left: 2.5rem;
    z-index: 100;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #aaa;
    text-decoration: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: #333; }

  /* ── Hero ── */
  .hero {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 2.5rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: 660px;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3.8rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    color: #0a0a0a;
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .hero-by {
    color: #bbb;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1.8rem;
    max-width: 540px;
  }

  .hero-credits {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #aaa;
    line-height: 1.8;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  /* ── Feature Image ── */
  .feature-image {
    width: 900px;
    height: 480px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #f0ede8;
  }

  .feature-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 30%;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── Main Content ── */
  main {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
    background: #fff;
    max-width: 660px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 5rem 2.5rem 6rem;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #aaa;
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 2.2rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: #0a0a0a;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
  }

  /* ── Image Pair ── */
  .image-pair {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  .image-pair figure {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .image-pair img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: #f7f7f5;
  }

  /* ── Full-width Figure ── */
  .full-figure {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .full-figure img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: #f7f7f5;
  }

  figcaption {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #bbb;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── Specs Table ── */
  .specs-block {
    margin: 3rem 0 2rem;
    padding-top: 2.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #ebebeb;
  }

  .specs-label {
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #aaa;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .specs-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .specs-table tr {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0;
  }

  .specs-table tr:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .spec-key {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem 0.75rem 0;
    color: #999;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    white-space: nowrap;
    vertical-align: top;
    width: 38%;
  }

  .spec-val {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    color: #333;
    line-height: 1.55;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  .status {
    color: #aaa;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #ebebeb;
  }
</style>
